# 1. Cloud-Deployed Application

## Project Overview

The primary objective of this project was to deploy a cloud-based application using multiple cloud services while ensuring security, scalability, reliability, and efficient resource utilization. The application architecture was designed using industry best practices to support real-world deployment scenarios.

The deployment included compute resources for hosting the application, cloud storage for managing application data, secure networking for communication between services, and Identity and Access Management (IAM) for user authentication and authorization. Security Groups and Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) were configured to restrict unauthorized access and maintain network isolation.

## Deployment Process

The deployment process consisted of the following stages:

* Provisioning cloud infrastructure.
* Configuring networking components.
* Creating Virtual Private Cloud (VPC).
* Configuring public and private subnets.
* Launching compute instances.
* Configuring Security Groups.
* Setting up Identity and Access Management (IAM).
* Deploying application code.
* Verifying connectivity and application functionality.
* Performing testing and validation.

Each deployment step was verified to ensure that the application functioned correctly while maintaining high security standards.

